esplanade reserve
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a strip of land along the foreshore, lake margins and river banks required to be set aside on any subdivision of land to protect conservation values and give public access for recreational use.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:Queen's Chain
Pronunciation:
Notes: See Resource Management Act 1991 ss 229ff.
